HARARE - Mystery surrounds MDC president Morgan Tsvangirai&rsquo;s emergency trip to South Africa amid swirling speculation that President Robert Mugabe&rsquo;s government paid for his chartered medical ambulance. Highly-placed sources told the Daily News yesterday that government paid for Tsvangirai&rsquo;s trip although it was not clear whether it had done so because of his status as former prime minister or it was a bail-out.